From Andrew Kille Subject Re Mary's assumption Dave Bernard wrote When Elizabeth greeted Mary Elizabeth said something to the effect that Mary out of all women was If so it appears that this exactly places Mary beyond the sanctification of normal The phrase is eulogemene su en gunaixin blessed are you among There is nothing to indicate that this is an exceptional or unique status only that as a woman Mary was Adding the word all is not a fair reading of the There are some good reasons for the church's veneration of Mary but they cannot depend on this